  <summary>01/09/1997--Introduced.
Federal Election Law Reform Commission Act - Establishes the Federal Election Law Reform Commission to recommend Federal election law reform. Requires a Federal election bill to be introduced in the House and the Senate within a specified time of the Commission's submittal of draft legislation or proposal for a constitutional amendment. Authorizes appropriations.</summary>
